<doc id="610544" wikidata="Q7069617" url="?curid=610544" title="Numbskull (song)">
<text>&quot;Numbskull&quot; is a single released by Ash on 26 April 1999 as a limited edition, individually numbered single of 5,000 on CD and double 7&quot; vinyl. The song, &quot;Numbskull&quot;, appeared as track 7 on the album, &quot;Nu-Clear Sounds&quot; (5 October 1998), and also as the final track on &quot;Intergalactic Sonic 7″s&quot; (9 September 2002).

The controversial video for the single was directed by Darran Tiernan and featured self-mutilation, sex, drugs and Wheeler naked.

